  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\r\nWe're currently doing a very strict check on [peer `EnrForkId`'s](https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/blob/81761c659f245878379fea2ce26d3ce4542cee03/networking/p2p/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/teku/networking/p2p/discovery/DiscoveryNetwork.java#L191-L200), which will reject peers whose next configured fork does not match out own.  In order to make the altair upgrade rollout smoother, we should probably accept any peer with a matching `forkDigest`.  It may also be worth suggesting [the spec ](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/765e994123c2e1fab8078acfb9e4b766b80d59a2/specs/phase0/p2p-interface.md#eth2-field) states that nodes `SHOULD` be lenient to allow for smoother upgrades. ",
